Kim Jong Il inspects Jagang Province 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) - General Secretary  Kim Jong Il gave on-site guidance to different fields of the national economy in Jagang Province from September 12 to 14.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Accompanying him were chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial committee of the WPK Yon Hyong Muk, secretaries of the WPK Central Committee Kim Kuk Thae, Kim Ki Nam and Kim Yong Sun and first vice department directors of the WPK Central Committee Pak Song Bong and Jang Song Thaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il visited Rangrim and Yonphung revolutionary museums, industrial establishments, newly-built minor power stations, co-op farms and other units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Going round Rangrim and Yonphung revolutionary museums, places associated with immortal exploits of the President Kim Il Sung during the anti-Japanese armed struggle and the Fatherland Liberation War, he expressed satisfaction at the fact that precious historic relics, the eternal treasure of the Korean revolution, have been well preserved, and posed for pictures with employees of the museums. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He also inspected the Jangjagang Machine Tool Factory, the September Textile Mill, the Kanggye Wine Factory, the Kanggye Garment Factory and the Kanggye Tilery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Looking round production processes of the factories, he said the militant spirit of the working class in Jagang Province, who are registering achievements braving difficulties, represents the revolutionary spirit of the heroic Korean working people with the faith in sure victory and indomitable will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He highly praised the workers at the Kanggye Wine Factory for having provided workers and other people in the province with wine and posed for a picture with innovators of the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Then he went to the Punam Youth Power Station in Hwaphyong county and a power station of the provincial public security bureau. He highly appreciated the feats of the builders who had greatly contributed to the improvement of the standard of the people's living in the mountainous region by generating much electricity through the use of valley water. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His inspection went to the Kanggye Aeguk Compound Microbiological Fertilizer Factory, the Janggang county township cooperative farm, the Rangrim county township cooperative farm, the sericultural breeding farm and a mulberry field of the Kanggye City Commercial Administration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He acquainted himself with the actual conditions of farming and research and production, going round the co-op farms and agricultural establishments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He met with women officials who devotedly work for the people, highly appreciated their deeds and posed for a photograph with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He put forward highly important tasks that would serve as a guideline in putting the economic affairs of Jagang Province on to a new higher stage and dramatically improving the standard of people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He highly praised Jagang Province for its unprecedented dazzling achievements in all aspects, including keeping production going. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said everywhere he went in Jagang Province he witnessed sky-high spirit and stirring realities, adding that the whole country should learn from the admirable fighting spirit of people in Jagang Province and the manner in which they manage economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He set forth tasks for keeping production going on a high-level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He underscored the need for all the industrial establishments in the province to make an effective use of production potentials so as to steadily increase production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He put forward the tasks related to electrification on a high level, growth of ligh industry and increased production in forestry, agriculture, sericulture and stock-raising. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He added that everything goes well in Jagang Province because the officials have a revolutionary fighting spirit and that wherever he went he saw the revolutionary leading  officials standing at the head of ranks.

Congratulatory visits to DPRK embassies
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- Dignitaries of different countries visited the DPRK embassies on September 9 to celebrate the 51st anniversary of the DPRK foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Among those visitors were secretary of the Egyptian presidency Sharf Riad, a special envoy of the President, and chief of the Royal Palace Sarda Prasad Pradan and secretary for information and external affairs of the Nepalese king Mohan Bahadur Pandey who were authorized by King Birendra Bir Bikram Shah Dev. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The secretary of the Egyptian presidency conveyed president Mohamed Hosni Mubarak's sincere greetings to General Secretary  Kim Jong Il, the government and people of the DPRK as well as his wish for the progress of the great Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The secretary for information and external affairs of the King of Nepal sincerely hoped that the friendly relations between Nepal and the DPRK would develop onto a higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, floral baskets and bouquets were sent to the DPRK embassies in different countries and the DPRK mission at the united nations on September 8-10 by Samsavath Lengsavath, deputy prime minister and Foreign Minister of Laos= the Commission for External Affairs of the central committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party= Cuban and Cambodian embassies in Laos= the department of foreign relations of the central committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Ministry of National Defence, the Ministry of Public Security, the Ministry of Transport and the Ministry of Culture and Information of Vietnam, the general bureau of diplomatic corps affairs of Vietnam, the Vietnam-Korea Friendship Association, the Vietnam-Korea Friendship Club, the Vietnam-Korea Friendship Kindergarten, the Ukrainian embassy in Hanoi= and the UN Children's Fund.

Brief history of Kim Jong Il introduced in Russia
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- A book on the brief history of General Secretary  Kim Jong Il's revolutionary activities was brought out in Russian by the Paleya-Mishin Publishing House on Sept. 8 on the occasion of the 51st anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Printed in its first page is a Portrait of Kim Jong Il.

DPRK's efforts for building powerful nation supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- The DPRK whose people advance with reliance on their strength in any adversity is sure to become a prosperous and powerful country, said the secretary general of the Italian Institute of International Relations, Giancarlo Elia Valori, who visited the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He noted that the Korean people are replete with high enthusiasm to fully discharge their mission for the times and revolution with beautiful dream and sure confidence in the future of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is the indomitable spirit and unshakable will of the Korean people to turn the country into a prosperous and powerful country by their own efforts at any cost although their way is thorny, he said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people have finished the "arduous march" and created a springboard of turn for prosperity and development of the country through the forced march of confidence and will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He stressed that the 21st century would be a new century of hope and glory in which the DPRK will brilliantly shine all over the world as a powerful nation under the great politics and wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Suppression of pro-reunification figures  slammed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- A few days ago, the South Korean authorities arrested Han Tong Gun, director of the secretariat of the "southern alliance of Kyonggi Province " under the "National Alliance for Democracy and Reunification" (Jongukryonhap) and two other persons by the notorious "National Security Law" on charges that they met without their approval figures of the north overseas to  hold a meeting on reunification and discuss the issue of withdrawal of the U.S. troops from South Korea and proposal on achieving national reunification by a confederal formula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Rodong sinmun today in a signed commentary assails this as an   anti-national and anti-reunification criminal move to check the tendency toward alliance with communism and the north and reunification now growing strong in South Korea as the days go by. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is an entirely just, natural and patriotic deed for the pro-reunification and patriotic figures of South Korea to have come out to achieve reunification through contacts with fellow countrymen in the north and solidarity and alliance with them, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is quite clear that the South Korean authorities do not want national reconciliation and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    Their suppression of figures of Jongukryonhap more saliently reveals the anti-national, anti-reunification nature of the ruling quarters of the "people's government who are doggedly pursuing only confrontation and division, going against the desire of the South Korean people for alliance with communism and the north and reunification.   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Public sentiments are the will of heaven. Therefore, those who are going against the sentiments for reunification will not be safe.

KCNA on war outburst of S. Korean  "Defence Minister"
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- "Defence Minister" of South Korea Jo Song Thae in an "interview" with Choogang Daily on Sept. 13 reportedly raised a hue and cry over "provocation" of someone and threatened to "check and repel it at all cost." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
   His outburst revealed once again a bellicose attempt to negate at whatever cost the Military Demarcation Line at the West Sea of Korea proclaimed in the special communique of the general staff of the Korean People's Army and spark the second bloody clash at the west sea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is nobody's secret that the June incident at the west sea which drove the peace and stability on the Korean peninsula to the worst phase was a premeditated armed provocation undertaken by the South Korean military at the instigation of the U.S. warhawks in a bid to launch aggression on the north and it was orchestrated by Jo Song Thae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is entirely intolerable for the top-class criminal like him who earned an ill-fame as a warhawk by orchestrating the west sea incident to repeatedly vociferate about the non-existent "provocation" of someone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   By nature he is a heinous warmonger always affected with war hysteria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Soon after taking his office as "Defence Minister " in late may this year, he "inspected" the headquarters of the three services of the army where he called for "establishing a perfect combat posture" to cope with an "all-out war" and a month later he orchestrated the west sea armed incident as the first scenario in the capacity of new "Defence Minister."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Yet, he is ballyhooing about "provocation" and "all-out surprise attack" of someone just like a thief crying "stop chief."  This sheer sophism can never be tolerated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If the enemy breaches the Military Demarcation Line at the west sea proclaimed by us, we will mercilessly wipe him out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   That will be neither "provocation" nor "surprise attack." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It will be an exercise of our legitimate right to self-defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean warhawks including Jo Song Thae are now inciting reckless confrontation with the north while letting loose a spate of provocative remarks slandering our just proclamation of the Military Demarcation Line at the west sea, but it is little different from a dog barking against the moon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The warhawks should ponder over the catastrophic consequences to be entailed by their reckless anti-north confrontation moves and refrain from committing  more serious crimes against the nation.

Japanese women call for normalized Japan-DPRK relations
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tokyo, September 14 (KNS-KCNA) -- A press conference was called here on Monday as regards the fact that Japanese women have decided to visit the DPRK and issued an appeal demanding the opening of Japan-DPRK diplomatic relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Addressing the conference were Sumiko Shimizu, social democratic member of the House of Councilors of Japan and representative of the Japanese Women's Liaison Council for Solidarity with the Korean women, and Mutsuko Miki, secretary of the forum on "Asian peace and women's role" who is wife of the former prime minister of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They explained the background against which a decision was made to dispatch a visiting group of Japanese women to the DPRK and an appeal was issued to call for turning relations between Japan and the DPRK into those of friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Referring to the three-point principled stand toward the present DPRK-Japan relations, which was clarified in the DPRK government's statement, the appeal said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Japanese government should lift sanctions taken against the DPRK with outcries over "missile launch," immediately resume negotiations for the normalization of Japan-DPRK relations and create an atmosphere for reconciliation between the two countries and peace in northeast Asia.

Three juggler brothers
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- The Moranbong Circus in Pyongyang is putting new magic pieces on stage in recent days, drawing a capacity audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Among them are "warrior dodging spears and swords," "rope-binding" and "trick with clock." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Three well known juggler brothers -- People's Artiste Kim Kwang Sok, and his younger brothers Kim Tong Sok and Kim Yong Sok are enthusiastically acclaimed by audiences for their bold and clever conception, graceful and dynamic movements and agile tricks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There is a moving story about how  sons of an ordinary worker became jugglers well known at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In his childhood Kim Kwang Sok liked to do gymnastics. He learned magic tricks when he was serving in the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In April, Juche 71 (1982) he had the Honor of presenting his skill before General Secretary  Kim Jong Il at the art festival of soldiers of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il praised him as a promising juggler, satisfied with his agile hand trick and saw to it that he joined a professional art troupe in November of that year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the subsequent period, Kim Jong Il saw his jugglery several times and gave detailed instructions on various aspects of performance from choosing themes to ways of representation.  At the same time, he made sure that Kim Kwang Sok's brothers were trained to be future jugglers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Kwang Sok and his brothers became jugglers under his loving care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Over the last decade they have produced and put on stage hundreds of magic pieces including "stabbing," "magic inside water and fire" and "treasure box."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They succeeded in creating and staging such peculiar pieces as magic drama "faith of soldier" and magic films "operation document" and "scout." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Kwang Sok came first at the 21st International Modern Magic Festival held in Karlovy Vary in Juche 76 (1987) and received the grand prix, the highest prize of the festival, and the festival cup and earned world reputation by receiving special prize and the "new technical creation prize" at the 3rd Wuqiao International Art Festival held in China in Juche 80 (1991). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He visited several countries including France and displayed his talent as juggler. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He and his brothers are now exerting themselves to produce more magic pieces of new themes and put them on stage.

Celebration held for publication
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, September 14 (KNS-KCNA) -- A meeting was held in Tokyo on September 11  to celebrate the publication of a collection of songs "Our future is bright" written by Han Tok Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Han Tok Su is the chairman of the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In his speech at the meeting So Man Sul, first vice-chairman of the Chongryon central standing committee, noted that bright is the future of the compatriots who are advancing in unity upholding General Secretary  Kim Jong Il, as the songs of the collection sing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  At the meeting the participants expressed their impressions on the songs of the collection. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In his speech at the meeting Han Tok Su said that in order to instill the national character into the new generation the Korean language and history and the advantages of the national culture of Korea should be well taught among them. He stressed his firm belief that the patriotic and national songs would resound through all parts of Japan in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   An art performance was given by artistes of Chongryon at the end of meeting.

Popular policy on dental treatment
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- A modern general dental hospital is now under construction on the Taedong River-side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Covering a plottage of over 28,000 square metres, the hospital will have all appliances and equipment for prevention and treatment including a diagnosis ward, outpatients' ward and sick-ward. When completed, it will make a great contribution to the promotion of people's health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All the health policies now in force in the DPRK serve that purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The dental prevention hospitals are found in every province (municipality) of Korea while the dental branch hospitals are housed by city and county people's hospitals across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   For example, the modern dental prevention hospital in South Hamgyong Province has well-equipped 170 treatment rooms and sick-rooms, tens of thousands of medical appliances and first-aid medical equipment of over 600 kinds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There are in the dental branch hospitals treatment rooms, preventive check-up rooms, dental prosthesis rooms and other professional rooms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All ri people's hospitals and dong clinics which are far from city and county seats have their own dentists.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President Kim Il Sung established a well-organized system of preventive dental treatment in the capital city and local areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President gave instructions six times as regards the dental treatment of the people on November 19 and 20, Juche 82 (1993) alone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He acquainted himself in detail with dental treatment and dental prosthesis and took relevant measures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He examined new all-purpose dental treatment equipment made by the Myohyangsan Medical Appliance Factory on June 25, Juche 83 (1994) before his demise and made sure that it was sent to all the dental hospitals across the country.

DPRK's efforts for building powerful nation supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 16 (KCNA) -- The DPRK whose people advance, believing in their own strength in any adversity, is sure to become a powerful country, said the secretary general of the Italian Institute of International Relations, Giancarlo Elia Valori, who visited the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He noted that the Korean people are replete with high enthusiasm to fully discharge their noble mission on behalf of the times and revolution with a beautiful dream and sure confidence in the future of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is the indomitable spirit and unshakable will of the Korean people to turn the country into a powerful socialist country by their own efforts at any cost although their way is thorny, he said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people have finished the "arduous march" and secured a springboard from which to make a turn for the prosperity and development of the country by conducting the forced march with confidence and will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He stressed that the 21st century would be a new century of hope and glory in which the DPRK will brilliantly shine all over the world as a powerful nation under the great politics and wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.
